observations.recommendation:
a) Provide the necessary support in enjoining all barangays to establish their own MRF;

b) Strictly enforce and intensify the information campaign on the no-littering policy among the residents;

c) Establish the sanitary landfill; and

d) Strictly comply with all other prescribed procedures and guidelines under RA No. 9003.

We reiterated our recommendation that the Municipal Mayor instruct the Inventory Committee to conduct and complete the physical count of the Municipality’s property and submit the RPCPPE to the Audit Team.
We also recommended that the Municipal Mayor:

a) Issue an office order creating An Appraisal Committee who will appraise the PPE which has no available information regarding its acquisition date and cost; and
b) Constantly monitor the status of physical inventory and the appraisal of PPE to ensure completion and submission of complete RPCPPE within the set deadline;

We also recommended that the Municipal Accountant to prepare and submit to the Audit Team the schedule of recorded PPE;

Require the Municipal Accountant and Municipal General Services Officer (MGSO) to make a reconciliation for the noted differences in the recorded PPE and RPCPPE;

Require the Municipal Accountant to submit to the Audit Team the request for relief from accountability with approval by the Commission on Audit (COA) – Commission Proper (CP) for the dropped PPE totaling P1,241,778.82; and

Require the accountable officer to pay the cost of PPE which were found missing/stolen totaling P16,000.00.

a) In-Charge of Office (ICO) - Municipal Treasurer (MT) to prepare the list of individual taxpayers with delinquencies for CYs 2002 to 2018 as December 31, 2018 and furnish it to the Municipal Accountant;

b) ICO-MT to prepare a statement of the reason or reasons for such non-collection or non-payment and submit it to the Sangguniang Bayan together with the list of taxpayers with delinquencies with a request for assistance in the enforcement of the remedies for collection provided in RA No. 7160 in order for the Municipality to have funds for other projects that will benefit its constituents; and

c) Municipal Accountant to prepare the necessary adjustments of RPT/SET Receivables once the list of delinquent taxpayers is received from the MT to reflect the correct balance of these receivables accounts.

a) ICO-MT to return to the Accounting Office the ten unclaimed/unreleased checks together with the DVs and supporting documents to facilitate proper adjustment in the books of accounts.

b) ICO-MT and Municipal Accountant to verify the existence and validity of the claims under the said 45 checks;

c) Municipal Accountant to make proper adjustments in the books of accounts by debiting and crediting the Cash in Bank account and crediting either the Accounts Payable, Prior Period Adjustments or the pertinent trust liability accounts once the validation of claims is complete;

d) ICO-MT to facilitate the replacement of the checks for valid claims and immediately deliver/remit the same to their respective payees.

a) Inventory Committee to complete the physical count of PPE;

b) MGSO to prepare a separate Inventory and Inspection Report of Unserviceable Property (IIRUP) for those with complete documents and prioritize its disposal thru sale by public auction or other modes of disposal to earn at least the salvage value of these assets; and

c) MGSO to prepare another IIRUP for those that can be individually identified by incomplete documents and thereafter require her to exert efforts to locate its documents.

a) Municipal Accountant and MBO to facilitate the transfer to TF of unutilized continuing appropriation totaling P1,800,000.00 because the project pertaining to P1,500,000.00 was already implemented and paid by TF while the project for the appropriation of P300,000.00 could not be implemented due to insufficient allocation;

b) Municipal Accountant to coordinate with the MBO or verify the relative records before processing any payment for PPAs under DRRMF to ensure proper accounting and recording of disbursements; and

c) MDRRMO – Designate to monitor the implementation and completion of the crucial PPAs of DRRMF for the benefit of Municipal constituents.
